Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and peel @carrots{12%ounce}; halve lengthwise and cut crosswise on a diagonal into
½-inch pieces. Strip leaves from @thyme{¼%ounce} stems; finely chop until you have
2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1};
thinly slice remaining half. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

== Honey-Roasted Carrots ==

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @honey{4%teaspoon},
¼ tsp chopped thyme (½ tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use more thyme later.)

Roast until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Couscous ==

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion
and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Israeli couscous{½%cup}; cook, stirring, until lightly toasted, ~{10-20%seconds}.

Add half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a big
pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until
couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess water if necessary. Stir in a pinch of lemon zest. Keep covered off
heat until ready to serve.

== Gravy-Smothered Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place in a #medium bowl{};
season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @flour{1%tablespoon},
½ tsp chopped thyme (¾ tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> Simply cook through this step as instructed, swapping in chicken for pork; cook,
> 3-5 minutes per side.

Melt 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in same pan over medium heat. Add sliced
onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil, remaining flour, and ¼ tsp chopped thyme (½ tsp for 4);
cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in 1 cup water (2 cups for 4), @beef stock concentrate{1}, remaining chicken stock
concentrate, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Bring to a simmer and
cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and
pepper to taste.

== Assembly ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous and carrots between plates. Top couscous with chicken and as much
gravy as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Slice pork crosswise if using pork instead of chicken.